Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the @butter{20%g} from your fridge and leave to one side to soften.

Chop the @sweet potato{2%unit} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop them
onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

While the sweet potato roasts, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and pop
them onto a piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{}, then season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel.

Once the sweet potato has roasted for ~{10%minutes}, place the tomato parcel
alongside (use another #tray{} if necessary). Cook for the remaining time.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @lentils{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Peel and
grate the @garlic cloves{3}(peeled, 1 grated for sauce, 2 for butter) (or use
a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot,
add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and cook until browned all over,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @korma curry paste{50%g} and half the garlic, stir-fry until fragrant,
~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @water{100%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and lentils. Bring to
the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the chicken is cooked through
and the liquid is reduced by about half, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's
> no pink in the middle.

While the lentils simmer, pop the softened butter into a #small bowl{} and add
the remaining garlic. Use a #fork{} to mash the garlic into the butter. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Halve the @ciabatta{1%unit}, then spread the garlic butter over the cut sides.

Once the lentils have reduced, stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g}. Simmer for
~{1%minute} more, then remove from the heat.

When the sweet potato has ~{5%minutes} of roasting time remaining, bake the
garlic ciabatta on the middle shelf of your #oven until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

When everything's ready, reheat the lentils (if needed), then stir in the
roasted sweet potato.

Add a splash more @water{} if you feel it needs it. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Share the creamy korma chicken and lentils out between your #bowls{}, then top
with the roasted tomatoes and any juices from the parcel.

Drizzle over the @mango chutney{40%g}. Cut the garlic ciabatta in half
diagonally and serve alongside. Enjoy!